Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the performance of routing protocols in mobile ad hoc networks, which is a subfield of networking. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The use of millimeter wave frequencies in wireless communications is a topic of interest in information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The use of millimeter wave frequencies is also relevant to multimedia applications, as it can provide high bandwidth and low latency. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Security is an important aspect of mobile ad hoc networks, and the paper may discuss the security implications of using millimeter wave frequencies. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may discuss the control and optimization of routing protocols in mobile ad hoc networks using millimeter wave frequencies.
